1
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,559
Hey kid, are you Li Kaiyang?

2
00:00:22,559 --> 00:00:23,760
Is your dad Li Tao?

3
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:25,960
Your mom's Wang Xinxin, right?

4
00:00:28,519 --> 00:00:30,079
Your parents were in a car accident.

5
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:31,839
They're in the emergency room right now.

6
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,159
Come on.

7
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:34,479
You don't believe me, huh?

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,719
This is your dad's ID, isn't it?

9
00:00:43,799 --> 00:00:44,920
Come with me, hurry!

10
00:00:45,159 --> 00:00:45,679
Move!

11
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:47,359
Go!

12
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:48,719
Hurry!

13
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:50,159
Let go of me!

14
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,280
Go, go, hurry!

15
00:00:51,479 --> 00:00:52,359
Let me go!

16
00:00:52,759 --> 00:00:54,079
You bad guys!

17
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:55,600
Open the door!

18
00:00:58,119 --> 00:00:59,240
Go, drive, now!

19
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:44,760
Dad.

20
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,040
Let me introduce you.

21
00:01:48,359 --> 00:01:50,799
This is Fengdu's brilliant detective,

22
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,000
my little case-cracking prodigy.

23
00:01:52,159 --> 00:01:52,879
Chief Jiang.

24
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,280
Little Kaiyang.

25
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:57,840
Is it really you?

26
00:01:58,719 --> 00:01:59,480
You've grown up.

27
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,040
You've really grown up.

28
00:02:01,879 --> 00:02:02,560
Mentor.

29
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:05,519
My dad's warmer to you than to me.

30
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,239
Why don't you give me a hug?

31
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,319
Why would I hug a brat like you?

32
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,080
Fine.

33
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:12,960
I worked up all those feelings for nothing.

34
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:16,960
Haven't you

35
00:02:17,759 --> 00:02:18,599
always wanted to know

36
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:19,719
why I can't let go

37
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,840
of the 5-3-1 case from 22 years ago?

38
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,199
There are too many mysteries involved.

39
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,639
And my mentor

40
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:28,680
always tells me only half the story.

41
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,120
Kaiyang,

42
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,960
Unravel the mysteries

43
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,000
in Jiang Han's heart.

44
00:02:41,639 --> 00:02:42,439
Come on, drag her in.

45
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,400
Hurry, hurry!

46
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,039
Faster!

47
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,360
I want my mommy!

48
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:56,400
Mommy! I want my mommy!

49
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:57,240
Keep crying,

50
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,560
Keep crying!

51
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,120
You little brat, crying the loudest.

52
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:03,759
Keep crying and I'll throw you in the river!

53
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,120
Stuff her in.

54
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:15,520
What are you staring at?

55
00:03:35,199 --> 00:03:36,199
After that incident,

56
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,680
my parents took me to another city.

57
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,120
Hoping I'd forget it all quickly.

58
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,120
But in the end,

59
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,080
I still chose to return to Fengdu.

60
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,520
Mentor, you should've told me sooner.

61
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,000
Maybe I could've talked you through it,

62
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,039
and helped you move past that shadow.

63
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,800
Jiang Han, watch your tone.

64
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:55,759
Chief Jiang.

65
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,400
Don't call me Chief Jiang.

66
00:03:57,639 --> 00:03:58,879
I've been retired for years now.

67
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,400
Uncle Jiang.

68
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,159
Jiang Han has a great personality.

69
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,000
He's straightforward.

70
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,319
Says whatever's on his mind.

71
00:04:06,639 --> 00:04:07,520
He really clicks with me.

72
00:04:07,879 --> 00:04:10,319
Mentor, you finally spoke your mind.

73
00:04:10,639 --> 00:04:11,319
Don't worry.

74
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,039
Between us, I'll always be straightforward.

75
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:15,360
As for me,

76
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:18,000
I had this rascal late in life,

77
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,439
and spoiled him rotten.

78
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:22,199
What? Spoiled me?

79
00:04:22,199 --> 00:04:23,120
Me, spoiled?

80
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:24,920
The calluses on my backside haven't faded.

81
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,800
This definitely counts as

82
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,480
the childhood trauma you gave me.

83
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:33,279
The 5-3-1 case was 22 years ago.

84
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,279
I've been hunting Red Gloves for 22 years.

85
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:37,800
But

86
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,279
still not a single trace of them.

87
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:45,600
Mentor,

88
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,399
falling into a hellhole like that,

89
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:49,199
how did you escape?

90
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,600
If it's too hard, don't talk about it.

91
00:05:05,399 --> 00:05:06,720
Kid, you've got dumb luck.

92
00:05:06,879 --> 00:05:07,759
The boss likes you.

93
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:09,360
Kneel down and kowtow three times.

94
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,800
From now on, you're one of us.

95
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:13,079
Endless wealth and glory await you.

96
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:17,879
Kneel! Kowtow!

97
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,839
Kneel! Kowtow!

98
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:21,800
I won't kowtow to bad people.

99
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:24,199
Mom and Dad will have you put in jail.

100
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,480
You've got a tough mouth, kid.

101
00:05:27,959 --> 00:05:29,000
Want me to break your legs?

102
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,319
And send you out begging on the streets.

103
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,040
The boss likes you so much.

104
00:05:52,639 --> 00:05:53,360
Hurry, call him Boss.

105
00:05:55,839 --> 00:05:56,439
Hurry up!

106
00:06:04,519 --> 00:06:05,240
Hurry!

107
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:16,240
The police are here!

108
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:21,759
Mentor,

109
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,920
Every time you mentioned Red Gloves before,

110
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,519
you'd react so strongly.

111
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,759
This time you opened the wound yourself,

112
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:29,959
yet you're surprisingly calm.

113
00:06:31,759 --> 00:06:33,040
The truth is, deep down,

114
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,560
you've always carried a fear of Red Gloves

115
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,959
and the guilt of letting him escape.

116
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,480
Slowly, all that pressure

117
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,639
became a wound that couldn't heal.

118
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:42,120
So you wrapped it tightly

119
00:06:42,279 --> 00:06:43,879
in layers of gauze.

120
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:47,120
Sealed up for so many years,

121
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:48,959
how could that wound ever heal?

122
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:49,839
Yeah.

123
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:53,639
You're right.

124
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:56,040
I should've opened the window long ago

125
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,319
and let it breathe.

126
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:01,079
Seems the detective spirit is inherited.

127
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,639
When will I ever sound so philosophical?

128
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,279
Oh.

129
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,199
Mentor, what happened next?

130
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,519
At the scene, we captured six suspects

131
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:42,360
and rescued 12 children.

132
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,199
Based on their confessions,

133
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:46,079
we apprehended five more suspects.

134
00:07:46,519 --> 00:07:47,879
But the ringleader, Han Dajun,

135
00:07:48,319 --> 00:07:49,279
still got away.

136
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:56,759
Little one,

137
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,439
don't be afraid.

138
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,360
We're the police.

139
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,759
Those damn traffickers were too cunning.

140
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,160
A month later,

141
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,160
we surrounded the ringleader, Han Dajun.

142
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:13,240
He then killed himself to escape justice.

143
00:08:14,079 --> 00:08:15,000
What about Red Gloves?

144
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:17,959
After Kaiyang woke up,

145
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,079
he told me about someone named Red Gloves.

146
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,680
But despite repeated searches,

147
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:24,600
we never found a trace of him.

148
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,639
It's been 22 years.

149
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,040
Red Gloves was like a drop of ink

150
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:31,759
dissolved into the deep sea,

151
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,960
completely vanished from the world.

152
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,159
I understand now.

153
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,519
Red Gloves' disappearance

154
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,039
became an indelible shadow in your heart.

155
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,200
And for my mentor too,

156
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,120
a boulder he couldn't lift from his heart.

157
00:08:46,639 --> 00:08:47,240
Mentor,

158
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,559
you became a detective

159
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,320
because of Red Gloves, didn't you?

160
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:54,879
Not entirely.

161
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,440
It had a lot to do with your father.

162
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,559
Uncle Jiang encouraged me.

163
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,519
"You're a born detective," he said.

164
00:09:04,159 --> 00:09:05,399
Xing Junfeng told me

165
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,200
that within six months on the force,

166
00:09:07,679 --> 00:09:09,080
you helped crack

167
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:11,320
a long-standing serial theft case.

168
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,080
And by following the leads,

169
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,279
you took down a huge fencing ring.

170
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,480
So Captain Xing moved me to Major Crimes,

171
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:19,840
under Captain Zhao's mentorship.

172
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,240
Jiang Han told me about the Red Gloves case.

173
00:09:22,879 --> 00:09:24,480
I've done some digging into Ma Shijiang.

174
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,639
How much do you know about his background?

175
00:09:28,679 --> 00:09:30,279
Ma Shijiang, a local.

176
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,519
His father is Ma Ping,

177
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:32,840
his mother is Qiu Huimin.

178
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,279
Both are ordinary office workers.

179
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:36,720
Qiu Huimin may be ordinary,

180
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:39,120
but her cousin certainly isn't.

181
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,600
The chairwoman of Jingwen Group,

182
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,919
Xu Wenwen.

183
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:43,960
What?

184
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:45,720
It all fits.

185
00:09:45,879 --> 00:09:46,600
Everything fits.

186
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,360
The map Captain Zhao drew before he died,

187
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,039
that was Xu Wenwen's club.

188
00:09:50,759 --> 00:09:52,360
The reason Ma Shijiang escaped

189
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:54,080
must be Xu Wenwen's doing.

190
00:09:54,399 --> 00:09:55,000
Uncle Jiang,

191
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:58,039
there's huge danger behind Ma Shijiang.

192
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,399
You shouldn't get involved.

193
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,679
Leave it to me and Jiang Han.

194
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,759
Yeah, Dad.

195
00:10:01,879 --> 00:10:02,960
You're getting on in years.

196
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,240
Age has nothing to do with it.

197
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,120
Though I've taken off the uniform,

198
00:10:08,279 --> 00:10:09,679
the mission and duty of a detective

199
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,840
are etched deep in my bones.

200
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,240
I'm not old yet.

201
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:14,320
I can still do this.

202
00:10:14,799 --> 00:10:18,000
If I see Red Gloves brought to justice,

203
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:20,600
I can die in peace.

204
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,080
Hey, what are you saying?

205
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,159
Uncle Jiang,

206
00:10:23,879 --> 00:10:24,960
do you know Xing Mingliang?

207
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,720
He went to high school with Ma Shijiang.

208
00:10:29,159 --> 00:10:30,399
And they were both involved

209
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,879
in molesting a female classmate.

210
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,159
It happened in their senior year.

211
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:35,960
Three boys were involved.

212
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,559
So how can we tell?

213
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,879
The details.

214
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,480
Some seemingly trivial details

215
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,279
often reveal a person's true mental state,

216
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:54,279
especially men with deviant tendencies.

217
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,639
For instance, in certain moments,

218
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,639
shifts in their gaze and expressions.

219
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,360
Clenching fists unconsciously when talking

220
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:04,000
suggests he's likely tense

221
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,159
or repressed inside.

222
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,200
Touching the nose unconsciously,

223
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,559
clearing the throat,

224
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,200
fiddling with clothing,

225
00:11:11,279 --> 00:11:12,919
these suggest he's likely covering up.

226
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:14,679
He's lying.

227
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,159
My little princess,

228
00:11:17,519 --> 00:11:18,519
wait for me at home.

229
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,960
I'll go buy hotpot base and be right back.

230
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:50,879
Xing Mingliang, the youngest, wasn't 16,

231
00:11:51,159 --> 00:11:53,039
so he was put on academic probation.

232
00:11:53,399 --> 00:11:56,279
The other two were 16, and were expelled.

233
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,039
One of them was Ma Shijiang.

234
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,039
Mentor.

235
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,679
You guessed right again.

236
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,519
This Xing Mingliang really is suspicious.

237
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,080
But based solely on the past incident,

238
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:06,200
there's no way to prove

239
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,840
Xing and Ma are directly connected,

240
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,759
or that Xing was involved in the crime.

241
00:12:11,159 --> 00:12:11,759
Exactly.

242
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,039
The year of the molestation case,

243
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:14,679
I was the deputy chief of police,

244
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:17,320
and Xing Junfeng led Major Crimes.

245
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,679
In a fit of rage,

246
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,759
he insisted on sending Mingliang to juvie.

247
00:12:21,279 --> 00:12:23,200
Mingliang was truly terrified back then.

248
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:25,840
He knelt and swore he'd never do it again.

249
00:12:27,879 --> 00:12:29,480
Judging from that,

250
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,399
Uncle Xing isn't one to shield his own.

251
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,039
Actually, Mingliang

252
00:12:33,039 --> 00:12:34,000
isn't bad at heart.

253
00:12:34,519 --> 00:12:36,600
It's just that his mother died too young,

254
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:38,320
and Xing Junfeng failed to discipline him.

255
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:39,759
That's what led to

256
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:41,480
his extreme personality.

257
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:43,919
Maybe

258
00:12:44,919 --> 00:12:46,519
he just learned to hide his emotions.

259
00:12:46,679 --> 00:12:48,120
Hmm, you know what?

260
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,080
After that incident,

261
00:12:50,279 --> 00:12:51,679
he became a completely different person.

262
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,720
Not only did his grades improve,

263
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,440
but also,

264
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,559
in swimming

265
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,480
and taekwondo,

266
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:58,120
he achieved great results.

267
00:12:59,559 --> 00:13:00,240
Swimming...

268
00:13:10,519 --> 00:13:11,279
Just as I thought.

269
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:13,720
He's a master of concealment.

270
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:18,559
Oh no.

271
00:13:19,679 --> 00:13:20,600
Ruolan is in danger.

272
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:21,879
I have to go, Uncle Jiang.

273
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,440
Mentor, Dad, we're heading out.

274
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,000
Okay.

275
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:21,799
Hello?

276
00:14:22,039 --> 00:14:22,720
Brother Li.

277
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:23,679
Ruolan.

278
00:14:25,039 --> 00:14:25,919
Has Mingliang come back?

279
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,679
No.

280
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:28,519
Ruolan.

281
00:14:29,559 --> 00:14:30,360
Don't panic, okay?

282
00:14:30,519 --> 00:14:31,240
Listen to me.

283
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,600
I'm on my way to you right now.

284
00:14:33,399 --> 00:14:34,080
Brother Li...

285
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,600
Red gloves.

286
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,039
There are so many red gloves.

287
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:40,000
Red gloves?

288
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,159
What happened?

289
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,399
So many red gloves.

290
00:14:45,399 --> 00:14:47,559
They're... they're in Mingliang's room.

291
00:14:55,399 --> 00:14:55,879
Hello?

292
00:14:56,919 --> 00:14:57,440
Ruolan!

293
00:14:58,639 --> 00:14:59,480
Ruolan, say something!

294
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:00,720
Ruolan!

295
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,279
Something's happened.

296
00:15:06,399 --> 00:15:07,159
Drive faster!

297
00:15:35,279 --> 00:15:36,679
Why aren't the comparison results back yet?

298
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,240
The test results show

299
00:15:38,679 --> 00:15:40,840
the blood on the knife is Su Zhuang's.

300
00:15:41,039 --> 00:15:41,679
What about the fingerprints?

301
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:42,879
Fingerprints...

302
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,320
The comparison results aren't back yet.

303
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:46,759
Sun Fei.

304
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,240
You've always been someone

305
00:15:49,799 --> 00:15:50,799
who speaks her mind,

306
00:15:50,799 --> 00:15:51,840
quick and decisive in action.

307
00:15:52,039 --> 00:15:52,960
What's gotten into you today?

308
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:57,360
What did you just hide?

309
00:15:59,679 --> 00:16:00,559
Speak up.

310
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:14,320
Why didn't you report this immediately?

311
00:16:15,799 --> 00:16:16,960
This is absolutely reckless.

312
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:31,600
Mister.

313
00:16:33,399 --> 00:16:35,240
Mister, the man across the hall just left.

314
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:36,039
When?

315
00:16:36,039 --> 00:16:37,679
I just bumped into him on my way home.

316
00:16:37,879 --> 00:16:39,480
He was carrying a really big suitcase

317
00:16:39,679 --> 00:16:40,759
and wearing a mask.

318
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:41,759
I called out to him,

319
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:42,799
but he ignored me.

320
00:16:42,919 --> 00:16:44,120
This is bad, Mentor.

321
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,320
Something must've happened to Ruolan.

322
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:46,080
Thank you.

323
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:47,480
Notify the team.

324
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,159
Get the security footage from management.

325
00:16:58,519 --> 00:16:59,080
Li Kaiyang.

326
00:16:59,080 --> 00:16:59,639
Brother Wang.

327
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,360
Break down Mingliang's door.

328
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,039
I'll get the surveillance footage.

329
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:04,519
Li Kaiyang.

330
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,599
Come back to HQ with me for questioning.

331
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:08,119
Ruolan is in trouble.

332
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,359
Her life may be in danger.

333
00:17:09,799 --> 00:17:10,519
After we save her,

334
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,759
I'll find a way to explain everything.

335
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:13,839
Captain Wang, according to his neighbor,

336
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:15,519
Ruolan was likely kidnapped by Mingliang.

337
00:17:15,799 --> 00:17:16,559
Li Kaiyang.

338
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,039
Forensics found your fingerprints

339
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,400
on the weapon used to kill Su Zhuang.

340
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:21,400
Per protocol,

341
00:17:21,559 --> 00:17:22,400
you must

342
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,279
come with me for questioning immediately.

343
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,839
Didn't I already tell you?

344
00:17:26,519 --> 00:17:27,839
I never touched that knife.

345
00:17:28,079 --> 00:17:31,079
That's why you need to cooperate with us.

346
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:33,200
Wang Yonglin.

347
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:34,720
Haven't you always boasted

348
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,400
about being a seasoned veteran detective?

349
00:17:36,799 --> 00:17:38,400
Can't you see how clumsy this setup is?

350
00:17:38,759 --> 00:17:40,359
If I'd killed Su Zhuang with that knife,

351
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:42,160
would I leave my prints on it,

352
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,240
toss it casually in the woods,

353
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,440
and wait for you to investigate me?

354
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,480
No matter how reasonable your explanation,

355
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,799
per protocol,

356
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:51,599
you must come back with me for questioning.

357
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,519
Don't force me to take coercive measures.

358
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,720
Come on, Captain Wang.

359
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,480
We're brothers who've been through hell.

360
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,240
Is this really necessary?

361
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,680
Jiang Han, stop interfering.

362
00:17:58,960 --> 00:17:59,440
Hold on.

363
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,440
Look at my mentor.

364
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,759
Look what this case has done to him.

365
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,000
If you take him away now,

366
00:18:03,119 --> 00:18:04,720
the real mastermind will get away with it.

367
00:18:05,079 --> 00:18:05,680
Jiang Han.

368
00:18:06,599 --> 00:18:07,960
Li Kaiyang's case

369
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,759
will be thoroughly investigated.

370
00:18:10,079 --> 00:18:11,920
But first, he must come back with us.

371
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,240
If you obstruct us further,

372
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,240
that's a violation of discipline,

373
00:18:15,359 --> 00:18:16,720
and it'll only deepen suspicion of him.

374
00:18:18,039 --> 00:18:18,640
Take him.

375
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:23,720
What are you all standing around for?

376
00:18:23,839 --> 00:18:24,400
Huh?

377
00:18:25,319 --> 00:18:26,039
Move.
